House Resolution 887
By: Representatives Blackmon of the 146th and Erwin of the 32nd
A RESOLUTION
1 Creating the House Study Committee on Reducing and Prioritizing Mandates for Public
2 School Administration; and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, providing for public education is a primary responsibility of the State of
4 Georgia, as enshrined in the Constitution; and
5 WHEREAS, local school systems are established and maintained and under the management
6 and control of local boards of education; and
7 WHEREAS, providing for the education of Georgia's public school students is a
8 responsibility shared by state and local governing authorities; and
9 WHEREAS, the effective administration of public elementary and secondary schools in this
10 state requires local boards of education, local school system administrators, and public school
11 administrators to address many and varied state and federal statutory and regulatory
12 mandates; and
13 WHEREAS, the addition of new legal mandates each year to existing mandates, some of
14 which have become outmoded or are practically unenforceable, can have the unintended
